Test Connectivity

[]

private/trading-cash/place-a-new-order.h.title: Place a New Order
private/trading-cash/place-a-new-order.h.body:
Place a New Order
This endpoint submits a request to place a new order from user's cash account.
POST api/v2/cash/order

API Key Permission: Trade

Requested Parameters:



FieldName
FieldType
Required
Default
Description
Value Range




coid
string
Yes
NA
a unique identifier of length 32 which consists of only lower case characters (a-z), upper case characters (A-Z) and digits (0-9)



time
long
Yes
NA
milliseconds since UNIX epoch in UTC, requests placed more than 30 seconds ago are treated as expired and will not be processed



symbol
string
Yes
NA
Trading symbol to trade



orderPrice
string
No
NA
required for limit orders and stop orders



stopPrice
string
No
NA
required for limit orders and stop orders



orderQty
string
Yes
NA
The quantity of the order



orderType
string
Yes
NA
the type of the the order
"limit", "market", "stop_markter", "stop_limit"


side
string
Yes
NA
trader's side
"buy", "sell"


postOnly
boolean
No
False
if true, the order will either be posted to the limit order book or be cancelled, i.e. the order cannot take liquidity
True, False


timeInForce
string
No
"GTC"
Currently, we support "GTC" (good-till-canceled) and "IOC" (immediate-or-cancel).
"GTC, "IOC"


sync
boolean
No
False
if true, the 'status' field in response will demonstrate the status of the order in matching engine  (note that it will slow down the response speed)
True, False




Response Content:



FieldName
FiledType
Description




coid
string
a unique identifier of length 32 (see above)


status
string
order stauts (see below)




Request body: application/json
Example:
{
    'coid': "98D98gzoVcE1U6UC7C7mupckj4rhOoJ0",
    'time': 1561043031451,
    'symbol': "BTH/ETC",
    'orderPrice': "0.0315",
    'stopPrice': None,
    'orderQty': "1.2",
    'orderType': "limit",
    'side': "buy",
    'postOnly': None,
    'timeInForce': None,
    'sync': None
}

Successful Response Example:
{
   'code': 0,
   'data': {'coid': '98D98gzoVcE1U6UC7C7mupckj4rhOoJ0', 'status': 'submitted'},
   'email': 'kuo.bao@test.com',
   'timestamp': 1561043031959
}

Other Info:

For this API you must include x-auth-coid in your request header.
Order status: An order may be in one of the following status in the matching engine: pendingNew(only available for stop orders), New, PartiallyFilled, Filled, Canceled, Rejected. If the status is 'submitted', it means the order is valid and has been received by the server. However, it doesn't imply that the order has been successfully submitted to the matching engine. If 'sync' field in request body is false, the 'status' field in response will always be 'submitted'. API users who want to know the status of the order in the matching engine should set 'sync' filed in the request body to be true (note that it will slow down the response speed and the 'status' field in response can still be 'submitted'). API users can always use the list open order API to monitor the status of the order placed.
API users should be careful about decimal places for oderPrice, stopPrice and orderQty. The number of decimal places for orderPrice/ stopPrice should not exceed priceScale, and that for orderQty should not exceed qtyScale, otherwise, they will be rounded. (prcieScale / qtyScale for each symbol can be obtained from API GET api/v1/products)

private/trading-cash/cancel-an-order.htm.title: Cancel an Order
private/trading-cash/cancel-an-order.htm.body:
Cancel an Order
This endpoint submits a request to cancel a cash account open order
DELETE api/v2/cash/order

API Key Permission: Trade

Requested Parameters



FieldName
FieldType
Required
Default
Description
Value Range




coid
string
Yes
NA
a unique identifier of length 32 which consists of only lower case characters (a-z), upper case characters (A-Z) and digits (0-9)



origCoid
string
Yes
NA
the coid of the order to cancel



time
long
Yes
NA
milliseconds since UNIX epoch in UTC, requests placed more than 30 seconds ago are treated as expired and will not be processed



symbol
string
Yes
NA
Trading symbol to trade



sync
boolean
No
False
if true, the 'status' field in response will demonstrate the status of the order in matching engine (note that it will slow down the response speed)
True, False




Response Content:



FieldName
FiledType
Description




coid
string
a unique identifier of length 32 (see above)


status
string
request status (see below)




Request body: application/json
Example:
{
    'coid': "lDk7dmxzPMc28ysU76ZfWlT7egaj5Vl4",
    'origCoid': "BqkMET6srJ7iou2p08wQUGKTf5dCtSi0",
    'time': 1561043163688,
    'symbol': "BTH/ETC", 
    'sync': None
}

Successful Response Example:
{
   'code': 0,
   'data': {'coid': 'lDk7dmxzPMc28ysU76ZfWlT7egaj5Vl4', 'status': 'submitted'},
   'email': 'kuo.bao@test.com',
   'timestamp': 1561043164195
}

Other Info:

For this API you must include x-auth-coid in your request header.
Note that you must use the cash account API to cancel cash orders and margin account API to cancel margin orders.
Request status: The status of a request to cancel a cash account open order can be 'Rejected', 'Canceled' or 'Submitted'. 'Rejected' means the request has been rejected and 'Canceled' means the cash account open order has been successfully canceled. If the status is 'submitted', it means that the request has been received by the server. However, it doesn't imply that the order has been successfully canceled in matching engine. If 'sync' field in request body is false, the 'status' field in response will always be 'submitted'. API users who want to know the status of the request should set 'sync' filed in the request body to be true (note that it will slow down the response speed and the 'status' field in response can still be 'submitted'). API users are highly recommended to use websocket to monitor the status of the order placed. 
Note that to allow clients to cancel immediately after placing an order, we do not check against open oders when user submits a request to cancel a cash account open order. It means that if there is no order in the matching engine whose coid is the origCoid in the request body, the response will still be a successful response instead of a failed resposne with error code and message.
